main event: A series of photographs depicting unidentified flying objects (UFOs) or aerial phenomena over a forested area in Albuquerque, New Mexico, taken on June 16, 1963.
interesting points: The photographs are part of a document from the Foreign Technology Division of the U.S. Air Force's Air Force Systems Command (AFSC), which was involved in investigating UFO reports.
The photographs show various disc-shaped or saucer-shaped objects partially obscured by trees and foliage, suggesting they were captured in a natural, forested setting.
Some of the photographs are blurry or of low quality, making it difficult to discern clear details about the unidentified objects.
In addition to the UFO photographs, the report includes images of vehicles and other natural landscapes, suggesting a broader investigation or documentation effort.
The documents are marked as 'UNCLASSIFIED', indicating they were either declassified or never classified in the first place.
sighted object: disc-shaped or saucer-shaped unidentified flying objects (UFOs)
photographs: yes, 26 photographs are included in the report
